  <brief_title>Tezacitabine and Oxaliplatin for the Treatment of Patients With Metastatic Colorectal Cancer</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Chiron Corporation</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Chiron Corporation</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary purpose of this study is to determine the best dose of tezacitabine when combined
      with oxaliplatin in patients with metastatic colorectal cancer. This study will also evaluate
      tumor response to the combination of anti-cancer drugs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
